      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: relay Claude CLI assistant partial messages as streaming deltas",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRelay Claude CLI assistant records as streaming deltas so the WebChat UI shows progressive output instead of waiting for the full response.\n\n**Fix 1**: Parse `assistant` records from the Claude CLI JSONL stream and forward their text content as `chat.delta` events.\n\n**Fix 2**: Gate on `stop_reason` using a positive partial signal: only forward records where `stop_reason` is explicitly present and `null` (the documented Claude CLI partial marker). Complete messages with `stop_reason: \"end_turn\"` are skipped to avoid duplicating the final message. Records without `stop_reason` at all are ignored as ambiguous (could be complete messages from custom `claude-stream-json` backends).\n\n## Changed files\n\n- `src/agents/cli-output.ts` -- Added `parseClaudeCliPartialAssistantDelta` with positive `stop_reason: null` guard\n- `src/agents/cli-output.test.ts` -- Tests covering partial forwarding, complete-message skip, absent-stop_reason rejection, and edge cases\n\n## Verification\n\nAll tests use the documented `stop_reason: null` marker for partial messages:\n- `stop_reason: null` (explicit) -> text forwarded as streaming delta\n- `stop_reason: \"end_turn\"` -> record skipped (complete message, not a partial)\n- `stop_reason` absent -> record skipped (not a confirmed partial; prevents false delivery from custom backends)\n- Non-assistant record types -> ignored by the parser\n- Malformed content arrays -> returns null without throwing\n- Mixed text + tool_use content -> text extracted, tool_use entries ignored\n\nRelated: #86050\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Claude CLI assistant records are not relayed as streaming deltas, so WebChat waits for the full response. The `parseClaudeCliPartialAssistantDelta` function requires a positive partial signal (`stop_reason: null` explicitly present) to skip complete messages and forward only true streaming partials as `chat.delta` events.\n\nReal environment tested: macOS 15.5, Node 24.3.0, OpenClaw built from branch `fix/gateway-stream-relay`.\n\nThe parser tightening addresses ClawSweeper [P1] finding: records without `stop_reason` are no longer treated as partials, preventing false delivery from custom `claude-stream-json` backends. Only records with the documented `stop_reason: null` partial marker are forwarded.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Claude CLI session with real streaming output over the gateway WebSocket connection. The fix is verified through unit tests against the documented Claude CLI JSONL protocol.\n",
